# .gitignore — RTD readout board (CRD + ADS1115, ratiometric)
# Rule (docs/DIRECTORY_MANAGEMENT.md): source is committed; anything a command can
# regenerate is ignored (fab/) or committed only as a report (reports/). Keep
# *.kicad_pro tracked (board setup / netclasses / rules = source); ignore *.kicad_prl
# (per-user local state).

# --- KiCad local / auto-generated ---
*-backups/
*.kicad_prl
_autosave-*
*-bak
fp-info-cache
*.lck
~*.lck

# --- Generated manufacturing outputs (cut at a tagged rev; never linger in-tree) ---
fab/

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/

# --- SPICE scratch (keep decks in sim/, final results in reports/sim; ignore scratch) ---
sim/scratch/

# --- Library verification scratch ---
libraries/_verify/

# --- Vendored reference: old REF200 project. Files are committed for reference; its
#     original git history is preserved on disk as .git.disabled but not tracked. ---
references/excitation-current-source/.git.disabled/

# --- OS / editor junk ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*~

# --- Claude Code local session settings ---
.claude/
